{"success": true, "message": "Fetched question.", "data": {"showTimer": true, "showAttemptInsight": true, "playSounds": true, "dontShowCorrectAnswerImmediately": false, "_id": "64c0e82e6f5bfc7ab78aeb49", "classes": [], "exams": ["615d7713c52ffa3c944600e3"], "subjects": ["615d708dbd4a37c4058ee5a8"], "chapters": ["615d6fed2b295b085ab6eba7"], "topics": [], "concepts": [], "previousYearPapers": [{"_id": "64c0e679aef333185c6bb44d", "title": "BITSAT 2022", "isVisible": true}], "position": 0, "type": "singleCorrect", "level": 3, "approximateTimeRequired": 180, "question": {"text": "A transistor is connected in common-emitter (CE) configuration. The collector supply is $8 \\mathrm{~V}$ and the voltage drop across a resistor is $500 \\Omega$ in the collector circuit is $0.6 \\mathrm{~V}$. If the current gain factor $\\alpha$ is $0.96$, find the base current", "image": null}, "options": [{"id": "ojJ9D", "text": "\r\n$25 \\mu \\mathrm{A}$\r\n", "isCorrect": false, "image": null}, {"id": "6Yk5h", "text": "\r\n$50 \\mu \\mathrm{A}$\r\n", "isCorrect": true, "image": null}, {"id": "rfbg7", "text": "\r\n$20 \\mu \\mathrm{A}$\r\n", "isCorrect": false, "image": null}, {"id": "MEtdp", "text": "\r\n$35 \\mu \\mathrm{A}$", "isCorrect": false, "image": null}], "correctValue": null, "solution": {"text": "Given, $V_{C C}=8 \\mathrm{~V}$\r\nVoltage drop, $V_0=\\Delta I_C R_L=0.6 \\mathrm{~V}$\r\nLoad Resistor, $R_L=500 \\Omega$\r\nGain factor, $\\alpha=0.96$\r\n$\\because \\quad \\beta=\\frac{\\alpha}{1-\\alpha}=\\frac{0.96}{1-0.96}=24$\r\nNow, $\\quad V_0=\\Delta I_C R_L$\r\n$0.6=\\Delta I_C \\times 500$\r\n$\\Delta I_C=\\frac{0.6}{500}=1.2 \\times 10^{-3} \\mathrm{~A}$\r\nNow,\r\n$\\beta=\\frac{\\Delta I_C}{\\Delta I_B}$\r\n$\\therefore$ Base current $\\Delta I_B=\\frac{\\Delta I_C}{\\beta}=\\frac{1.2 \\times 10^{-3}}{24}=5 \\times 10^{-5}$\r\n$=50 \\times 10^{-6}$\r\n$\\Delta I_B=50 \\mu \\mathrm{A}$", "image": null}, "videoSolution": null, "numericalUpperLimit": null, "numericalLowerLim